# 4. アイドルといえば初日の出！？

Minori: Huff... Huff... H-How much more until the summit...?
Comments: <You can do it, Minori!> <Just a little bit more! I think...> <I've climbed this mountain before. I know it's tough, but I believe in you!>
Minori: You guys...!
Minori: Thanks! I'm gonna keep trying my best!
Haruka: It's supposed to get pretty steep from here, so let's pause the stream for now and resume when the trail's a little flatter.
Shizuku: Right. We wouldn't want to fall anywhere along the way.
Airi: Then, we'll see you all in a bit! Stay tuned to see the first sunrise of the new year!
Comments: <I can't wait to see the sunrise with MMJ!> <I can't wait to see the sun that is Shizuku!> <Wow, Haruka seems totally fine. Keep it up, girls!>
Minori: Thanks! See you soon!
Airi: And... Pause. Just a bit more until the summit, so let's keep at it!
Minori: Yeah!
Miku: <How's it going, girls?>
Minori: Oh, Miku! You came to check up on us?
Rin: <We're here too♪ Oh, are you almost at the top?>
Airi: Yup. We should be there pretty soon.
Len: <Then, we came at just the right time. Also, this is such a great idea for a stream.>
KAITO: <I agree. Not many people would say, “Let's stream the first sunrise from the top of a mountain so everyone can watch!”>
Shizuku: We need to thank Minori for saying how she wanted to see it with Haruka.
Minori: Hehe. All I did was suggest something that I wanted to do...
Rin: <But this trail's so dark... Are you gonna be okay?>
Airi: Yup! We looked this place up before we came, and made sure to bring lights and other hiking gear.
Haruka: We also picked the easiest trail since it seemed like the most beginner-friendly.
Haruka: Not only that, you can actually reach the summit by car, so we can always try calling for one if something does happen.
Airi: Plus, it's supposed to be easy to film up top because there's supposed to be this nice, flat plaza!
Luka: <I see... Oh, I hear some other people talking. You must be close to the summit now.>
MEIKO: <Yes, but don't let up now. You need to keep pushing until you're all at the top!>
Minori: Right!
Airi: Alright, now that we all seem ready, why don't we resume our stream?
Airi: We're back, everyone! And we've almost reached the top!
Comments: <Welcome back!> <Oh, I see some light. You must be close.> <You can do it MMJ!>
Haruka: Thanks, everyone!
Haruka: Oh, Shizuku, the frosted parts are very slippery, so take it slow and move one step at a time.
Shizuku: Okay! I'll be careful not to slip...
Minori: Hey, look! I think I see the summit...!
Airi: Yeah, me too! Alright, just a little bit more to go...!
Minori: Wow...!
Comments: <The sky's so pretty!> <The sun looks like it's about to come up!> <Nice timing!>
Haruka: Hehe... I'm glad we got here in time.
Shizuku: Me too. And getting to welcome in the new year with all of our fans fills me with so much joy.
Airi: Let's all wish for this year to be a great one!
Minori: Yeah! I'm gonna ask the sun to make sure all of you guys also get to have an amazing year! Hnng...
Comments: <Her “Hnng” face is so cute lol.> <Thanks for wishing on our behalf, Minori!>
Haruka: Hehe. Then, why don't we all make a wish so that tomorrow is a better day for everyone?
Airi & Shizuku: Okay!
Comments: <I wish MORE MORE JUMP! will become more and more famous!> <I wish for all of you to have a really amazing year!>
Airi: Okay, let's cap things off by presenting our New Year's resolutions!
Minori: Yeah! So, mine's...
???: “Hah hah hah hah!”
Minori: Huh...? That voice... It sounded really familiar...
Tsukasanosuke: “Now, to make the people of this village smile!”
Lion Dance Deity: “CHOMP!”
Comments: <Isn't that Wonderlands×Showtime from PXL?> <What are they doing on top of a mountain?>
Shizuku: Oh, are they doing a show here? That's so wonderful...!
Airi: Yeah, on top of a mountain too... I guess that's one way to kick off the new year.
Lion-Dog: “Alright, let's work together to make everyone here smile!”
Haruka: Oh, I see. The story is about traveling across Japan to put smiles on everyone's faces with their show...
Tsukasanosuke: “Now, I am happy that the Lion-Dog has decided to join me, but it would be nice to have a bigger cast for our performances... And a larger audience...”
Lion-Dog: “Oh, I know...! Why don't we gather up a bunch of people and see who if any of them want to join us?”
Tsukasanosuke: “Yes, I see. If we gather enough people, then someone will likely ask to join our little troupe.”
Tsukasanosuke: “Someone! Anyone! Who out there can dance?! Who would like to perform alongside us?!”
Shizuku: So, are they asking for volunteers from the audience...?
Minori: Yeah, looks like it! Oh, some people are commenting on it...!
Comments: <That looks fun!> <Cool! You can just jump right in!> <I love these kinds of shows!>
Comments: <MMJ should volunteer!>
Airi: Oh, since we're here, why don't we give them a hand?
Minori: Huh? Lend them a hand? How?
Airi: Hehe. Like this...
Tsukasanosuke: “Is there no one out there who can dance for us...?!”
Dancer: “You rang?!”
Tsukasanosuke: “Hm?! I thought I just heard the lovely voices of some...”
Dancer: “W-We're dancers who live in this village!”
Dancer: “If it appeases you, may we join your performance?”
Tsukasa: (What? Hanasato and Shizuku?! Wait, hang on... It's all of MORE MORE JUMP!)
Tsukasanosuke: “Splendid! In that case, why don't we dance together?!”
Tsukasa: Rui, I hope you have some music ready!
Rui: Hehe. Don't worry. I've saved thousands of songs to Robo-Nene's memory to make sure we have something to play for anyone who volunteers.
Rui: So, since we have MORE MORE JUMP! here with us... Let's play... This♪
Airi: This song! It sounds similar to ones by that idol group with a traditional Japanese theme, Miko Miko☆Party!
Haruka: Hehe. Did they choose this just for us?
Shizuku: If that's the case, we'll need to put on the best dance performance we can!
Minori: I-I'm nervous about improvising a dance routine, but if it means putting smiles on everyone's faces...!
Airi: Okay, here we go! Viewers, get ready to be blown away!
Airi: Because you're all about to witness a never-seen-before joint performance by MORE MORE JUMP! and Wonderlands×Showtime!
Mountain Climbers: Huff... Huff... Darn, the sun's already up... Huh? I'm hearing music coming from the summit.
Mountain Climbers: Hey, there're people dancing! Is there an event or something?
Dancer: “Let's clap along together, everyone! We have to get the attention of everyone up above!”
Dancer: “So, we need to have as much fun as possible to start off the new year!”
Dancer: “Keep clapping, everyone! Let's all have as much fun as we can!”
Mountain Climbers: Hey, isn't that Haruka Kiritani...? And Shizuku Hinomori?! What are they doing here?!
Mountain Climbers: I have no idea, but it looks like fun... Let's go jump in!
Dancer: “You're all doing great! Next, raise your arms as high as you can! This should help you get refreshed!”
Dancer: “Ready, everyone? Here it goes!”
Mountain Climbers: “Yeah!”
Tsukasa: (Their energy...)
Tsukasa: (We sometimes ask the audience to clap along during our shows, but they're on a completely different level...)
Tsukasa: (However, they are idols. They excel at interacting and making connections with their fans, so I suppose it's only natural for them to get the crowd so excited.)
Tsukasa: (But I can't let them hog all the glory!)
Tsukasanosuke: “Alright, we must let the New Year's deity know that we are here! Everyone, young and old!”
Tsukasanosuke: “That, of course, includes our lovely dancers!”
Dancers: “Yeah!” “Yes!”
Rui: Hehe. Things are going very well. I believe you're up soon, Nene.
Nene: Right. Here I go...!
Tsukasa: Now, I would like to finish by wishing all of you a Happy New Year!
Tsukasa: And please give a big thanks to our young ladies! We were able to put on a spectacular show because of you!
Emu: Bye bye! See you all again sometime!
Shizuku: They left immediately after wishing everybody well...
Airi: I have a feeling that they're heading off to their next stop to do another show. We can properly thank them later when we get a chance.
Minori: Still, we danced a lot...
Haruka: We climbed a mountain and danced up a storm... It's been a really fun New Year's.
Comments: <WXS×MMJ was so awesome!> <I wanna live in this village!> <You guys were so cool!>
Comments: <MMJ was so cute as villager girls!> <I can't believe you improvised all of that!> <Talk about being blown away to start the new year!>
Airi: Hehe. Sounds like you all enjoyed the show!
Shizuku: Thanks to Wonderlands×Showtime, our stream became something even more special.
Haruka: Yeah, it did. I'd love to keep spreading hope to everyone like this moving forward.
Minori: Me too!
Minori: So! Let's keep trying more and more and more this year too!
